Controversial prophet, Shepherd Bushiri and his wife fled from South Africa to Malawi after being granted bail last year. JOHANNESBURG - Controversial prophet, Shepherd Bushiri's daughters and mother-in-law have reportedly been stopped from leaving Malawi for Kenya. Bushiri and his wife fled from South Africa to Malawi after being granted bail last year. READ: Bushiri extradition papers signed They're facing charges of theft, money laundering and fraud in connection with an alleged R100-million investment scheme.